description: When working with Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) or looking for historical arch choices
globs: docs/adl/**/*.md
alwaysApply: false
---

All Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) are located within `docs/adl`. Each ADR follows the MADR format.

When creating or editing ADRs, use the structure in `docs-adr-template.mdc` and follow the documentation writing style in `docs-writing-style.mdc`.

The valid statuses for an ADR include: PROPOSED, ACCEPTED, and RETIRED.

You should *not* use RETIRED ADRs to inform your choices; you should get the user's confirmation before acting upon PROPOSED ADRs.
